Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The ANC says it won't lodge a motion of no confidence against President Jacob Zuma. The governing party has however, resolved to recall him as the president of the republic. This was announced at a media briefing held at ANC headquarters, Luthuli House, in Johannesburg on Tuesday. ANC president Cyril Ramaphosa was dispatched, alongside the party's secretary-general, Ace Magashule, to inform the president of the NEC's decision at his residence, Mahlamba Ndlopfu, at around 10.30pm on Monday. Magashule, revealed that the president agreed to respect the NEC's decision. He said Zuma did however request more time at the Union Buildings.". eNCA